   TOBACCO ANTITRUST APPEAL: Brooke Group Ltd., formerly
Liggett Group Inc., sought reinstatement of a $148.8 million
jury award in its predatory price discrimination case against
Brown &amp; Williamson Tobacco Corp. After an eight-month trial,
the jury in Greensboro, N.C., had found that Brown &amp;
Williamson competed illegally in the market for low-priced,
generic cigarettes. Brown &amp; Williamson argued at trial and in
its motions to the judge that its price-cutting benefited,
rather than harmed, competition. Brooke is appealing a
federal trial judge's decision last month overturning the
verdict.
   ---
   BOSTON MERGER: Gaston &amp; Snow, a 305-lawyer corporate firm,
will merge with Csaplar &amp; Bok, which represents institutional
investors, among other clients. All of Csaplar's 17 partners
and 30 associates and staff attorneys are expected to join
Gaston &amp; Snow, effective Oct. 1. The new firm, based in
Boston, will be called Gaston &amp; Snow.
